<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:lang="en-US" xml:id="geogebra-lines-slope-y-int-from-standard">
  <title>Determine the Slope and <m>y</m>-Intercept of a Line Whose Equation is Stated in Standard Form.</title>

  <figure xml:id="geogebra-lines-slope-y-int-from-standard-geogebra">
    <caption>State the slope and <m>y</m>-intercept of the line that corresponds to the given equation after first isolating <m>y</m>.</caption>
    <interactive platform="geogebra" width="100%" aspect="9:5">
      <slate surface="geogebra" aspect="9:5" source="geogebra/lines-slope-from-equation.ggb">
        setPerspective("G");
        setGridVisible(0); 
        setAxesVisible(0,0);        
      </slate>
    </interactive>
  </figure>

</section>
